Text.Value: Do you like it? It was bestowed upon me as a reward.
But... fine. As you will. My own plans lie ruined back in that inn, amidst the corpses of my Harpers.
Pick one. Whichever is quicker. And do it now.
It can do far more than that. Far worse than that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tone here is grave, contained alarm. She's just seen us take the Slayer form - this is her first inkling that we might be a Bhaalspawn, and she's not sure we know it.

Text.Value: I fear we do not have the luxury of time. Last Light has fallen - we alone remain to stop Ketheric from marching on the city.
And hoped never to again.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tone here is grave, contained alarm. She's just seen us take the Slayer form - this is her first inkling that we might be a Bhaalspawn, and she's not sure we know it.

Text.Value: To earn a meeting where you will face him alone, at the height of his powers?
You have already made that choice. You returned Ketheric's relic to him. Perhaps you won his favour - but now you must face the full force of his power, alone.
Ketheric's power stems from the Nightsong - a relic that his necromancer, Balthazar, is trying to reach.
Ketheric's power stems from a relic in a Sharran temple: his pet necromancer is trying to reach it.
Once Ketheric is without his shield, the sword: together we assault his tower, and put a final end to this blight.
No reward, I promise you. A curse.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tone here is grave, contained alarm. She's just seen us take the Slayer form - this is her first inkling that we might be a Bhaalspawn, and she's not sure we know it.

Text.Value: It came to me in a dream.
You've seen it before.
No. I sent the Nightsong back to Ketheric to earn myself an audience.
I need a little time. But I will gladly join you at journey's end - so long as it leads to the grave of General Ketheric Thorm.
Surely you can join me on the road.
The time for words will come, when we lay my Harpers to their final rest. I owe them that.
It is you who holds the key to defeating Ketheric, not I. Do what you must. If it rids us of this cult, we'll consider the price well-paid.
So. What now?
I sent Ketheric's relic back to him - to earn myself an audience.
I discovered the source of Ketheric's invulnerability: a celestial called the Nightsong.
This relic must be your focus instead, then. Find it. Strip him of its power.
I suppose this place is no worse for wear than my last lodgings. Though I cannot say the same for myself, I fear.
Yes? You have news?
Once Ketheric is dealt with... then. Then we shall speak of this.
Nothing to report yet.
Does it matter? It's powerful - it can help us against our enemies.
No dream, then. A nightmare.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tone here is grave, contained alarm. She's just seen us take the Slayer form - this is her first inkling that we might be a Bhaalspawn, and she's not sure we know it.

Text.Value: Leave.
You've learned so much? That tadpole in your head already begins to pay dividends.
You know your task. This relic - find it. Strip Ketheric of its power.
The battle, the escape after... I might need to lick my wounds a while, before I can be of use to you.
Well done. Did you learn how we might untether Ketheric from this Nightsong?
What?! So all this time, he has been leeching his life from an immortal? The man is more parasite than anything in his True Souls' heads.
I've earned an audience with the Absolute. Are you well enough to join me?
Remove her from her bonds, or kill her, maybe. I haven't done either.
What?! So all this time, he has been leeching his life from an immortal? The man is more parasite than that thing in your head.
Do you want to talk about what happened at Last Light?
Where you will face him in the height of his power - alone.
That... form you took. That was no common shape-change. Where did you learn to do such a thing?

EditorData.NodeContext: Tone here is grave, contained alarm. She's just seen us take the Slayer form - this is her first inkling that we might be a Bhaalspawn, and she's not sure we know it.

Text.Value: Then by all means, don't let me keep you. We can't end this until Ketheric can bleed. I await your next report.
Once we've reached the city... then. Then we shall speak of this.
'Sent'? Meaning you had the source of all of Ketheric's power in your grasp, and you gave it back to him?
I'm still investigating that.
But first - I owe them justice. Moonrise must fall.
You know your task. Ketheric Thorm clawed his way free of death. Find out how, so we can send him back.
It must mean... but no. Not here. Not now. We have more pressing concerns before us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Almost to herself, stating that Bhaalspawn are back. But shaking her head - this isn't the time or place, and she needs to think.

Synopsis: Jaheira camp holding pattern until SCL is done, if Haven was attacked.
